<paragraph blockId="36.[138,1185,1565,1685]" pageId="36" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis box="[138,280,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="299">Relationship.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Watabe &amp; Gao &amp; Takamori &amp; Zhang &amp; Aotsuka, 2005" authorityName="Chen &amp; Watabe &amp; Gao &amp; Takamori &amp; Zhang &amp; Aotsuka" authorityYear="2005" box="[597,864,1565,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ailaoshanensis" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Amiota">
<emphasis box="[597,625,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="299">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[654,681,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="299">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[711,864,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="299">ailaoshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[883,986,1565,1589]" pageId="36" pageNumber="299" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the general morphology of male genitalia, especially paramere and aedeagus, but can be distinguished from it by the vertical lobe of gonopod basal two-thirds quadrate (roundish in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Watabe &amp; Gao &amp; Takamori &amp; Zhang &amp; Aotsuka" authorityYear="2005" box="[169,322,1661,1685]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Amiota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ailaoshanensis">
<emphasis box="[169,322,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="299">ailaoshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
